------------------------------------------------------------------
Test Char Weapon Help         By: Bullseye a.k.a Scyrus
------------------------------------------------------------------
Ok, now we're going to cover how to load a weapon for your test
char, then transfer it.  First let me tell you about the weapon
and what you can do with it:

------------------------------------------------------------------
Weapon Commands:
------------------------------------------------------------------
  setq - Set the quality of the weapon
Syntax: setq <amt>
------------------------------------------------------------------
  setwc - Set the class of the weapon
Syntax: setwc <amt>
------------------------------------------------------------------
  settype - Sets the type of the weapon
Syntax: settype <none|slash|pierce|cleave|blunt|pole|missile> 
------------------------------------------------------------------
  setid - Sets the alias of the weapon
Syntax: setid <new alias>
------------------------------------------------------------------

Ok, now to cover how to load the weapon, all you need to do is type
the following string:

clone /objects/testchar/test_armor.c

Simple enough.

Now to transfer the object to your test char, to do this just type
the following command, changing "scyrus" to "thenameofyourtestchar"

execute move_object(present("weapon", this_player()), find_player("scyrus"));
